It has the characters of the former, viz, a marginal zone wit-h a special structure, but the loculi some- times are small, the whole valve then getting very similar to that 01 a Stephanoclz'scus.

From Steph. astraea it is easily distinguished by the single rows 01 rather coarse puncta. In a fossil state, the valves generally have the aspect shown hy fig. 70 d.
